## Context

- arid1a-pancancer-sl-atlas: All 5 phases implemented and committed
- Phase 1: 173 ARID1A-loss lines, 11 qualifying cancer types
- Phase 2: ARID1B is dominant SL (d=-2.26 Lymphoid), not EZH2. 17 genes tested.
- Phase 3: 6,381 nominal genome-wide SL hits, 124 universal genes. WRN, ARID2 notable.
- Phase 4: Only 3 PRISM drugs found (CPI-1205, EPZ020411, tucidinostat). Limited validation.
- Phase 5: ~157K US patients/yr. Top recommendations: Lymphoid, Breast, Bladder, Esophagus/Stomach.
- No FDR-significant results due to small mutant group sizes — expected, nominal results are consistent.
- All outputs in data/results/arid1a-pancancer-sl-atlas/phase1-5/
- Code in src/cancer/arid1a_pancancer_sl_atlas/01-05_*.py
